##### Claude Code (local tooling) #####
# Ignore everything under .claude/ EXCEPT the project's curated, project-authored
# tooling, which is shared for reproducibility (git add it explicitly):
#   - .claude/agents/                    (the Coder/Tester/Reviewer subagents)
#   - .claude/skills/code-test-review-loop/   (the project-authored orchestration skill)
# Worktrees are machine-specific full repo copies; vendored/installed skills
# (e.g. posit-dev) are reinstallable via `npx skills add` and not committed.
.claude/*
!.claude/agents/
!.claude/skills/
.claude/skills/*
!.claude/skills/code-test-review-loop/

# Skills CLI store (`npx skills`): the real content that .claude/skills/ symlinks
# into. Machine-local; reconstructable from skills-lock.json (which IS tracked).
.agents/

##### Misc local artifacts #####
__pycache__/
R/EMC2_ARTICLE__replication_code.R
